The paper introduces a new centrality index for bipartite networks of papers and authors, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper discusses the use of the Web of Science platform, which is commonly used in information retrieval (IR) research. The paper also discusses the use of clustering, which is relevant to machine learning and data mining (cs.SD). The paper's focus on scientific social recognition and citation performance is relevant to digital libraries (cs.DL) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper's use of the Hirsch $h$-index is relevant to social informatics (cs.SI).
